snippet.textDisplay:
I have really bad psychogenic nonepileptic seizures when I try to fall asleep, and we don't yet know what causes them, but we have figured out that watching movies and videos and stuff can prevent them by distracting my brain by hearing words and sensing shifting light.
Usually I use some of your videos, but this one was such a trip. When I'm falling asleep and listening to words, my head still translates them, but in a really groggy state.
So essentially, my experience was summed up as: "Is that Amanda? doggie B???? Boogie sharks!!!"
